<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Ha.  Funny you mention this.

Was bored all day long so I went to South Karana, the camp was free, so I hitched up my little gold pants (I hate high elven fashion..) and sat.

Finally, the stupid thing spawned.  I called in some help from some guildmates (just in case Live decided to make an appearance as well) and waited.  It despawned.  And spawned again.  And despawned again.

Then, the putrid skele spawned one more time.

Last spawn I was going to sit for.

And I get a beg from the "newbie" that was running around pulling skeles, that accidently pull Drah, for a rez.

Not only that, but another cleric that was there camping it and I was grouped with, was actually higher than me.

The Iksar Shaman had the audacity to ask me "which was better, yours or hers."

He was level 16 by the way.  And BEGGING for a rez, complaining that his "high level paladin was camped here waiting for Grimrot as well."  Finally I turned him down because he simply demanded it, he felt in needed because he was a twink of his high level pally, and in the 40 minutes he waited there, he could have easily gone to Lake Rathe and made the experience up.

So he killed my placeholder.  Nothing I could do to stop it.  No fear memmed, nothing to be able to get him to stop. I've had a LOT of things stolen from me, I've done tons of free rezzes, heals, buffs, I don't charge for pinzarn in certain groups, and this "high level paladin" had the NERVE to destroy the only chance I will most likely have at having him spawn.

Machia Velli
44th year Priestess
Sol Ro
"Have rez, will travel, will be screwed."</TEXTAREA>
